The Telegraph - Calcutta : Frontpage
 Thursday, February 26, 2004 				 Teacher sops
 A STAFF REPORTER																								Guwahati, Feb. 25: The Assam cabinet tonight approved several pre-poll sweeteners.																								In a move to pacify agitating teachers, the cabinet decided to provide grants to teaching staff of the non-provincialised schools, sources said.																								Other sops include releasing salaries of schoolteachers in Sivasagar district.																								The government also sanctioned the attachment of 262 employees of the defunct minor irrigation department with the states irrigation department and approved 308 applications for VRS. The cabinet gave its nod to the states women, agriculture and cane and bamboo policies.
